## 4. Rule Statements (Building Blocks)

### Match Statements

| Statement type | What it checks | Example |
|---------------|----------------|---------|
| **ByteMatchStatement** | String match on a request field | Host header exactly equals `app.example.com` |
| **IPSetReferenceStatement** | Source IP is in an IP set | IP is in `my-internal-ip-set` |
| **GeoMatchStatement** | Source country | Country is US, IN, etc. |
| **SizeConstraintStatement** | Size of a field (body, URI, etc.) | Body > 10KB |
| **RegexPatternSetReferenceStatement** | Regex match on a field | URI matches `^/api/v[0-9]+/` |
| **SqliMatchStatement** | SQL injection detection (managed) | Query string contains SQL injection |
| **XssMatchStatement** | Cross-site scripting detection | Body contains XSS patterns |
| **RateBasedStatement** | Request rate from one IP | > 1000 requests in 5 min |

### Fields You Can Match On

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| **SingleHeader** | A specific HTTP header (e.g. `Host`, `User-Agent`, `Authorization`) |
| **UriPath** | The URI path (e.g. `/api/v1/users/`) |
| **QueryString** | The query string (`?key=value`) |
| **Body** | The request body |
| **Method** | HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.) |
| **AllQueryArguments** | All query parameters |

### Match Types (for ByteMatchStatement)

| PositionalConstraint | Meaning |
|---------------------|---------|
| **EXACTLY** | String must match exactly |
| **STARTS_WITH** | String starts with the value |
| **ENDS_WITH** | String ends with the value |
| **CONTAINS** | String contains the value |
| **CONTAINS_WORD** | String contains the value as a word |

### Text Transformations

Applied before matching. Common ones:

| Type | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| **NONE** | No transformation |
| **LOWERCASE** | Convert to lowercase |
| **URL_DECODE** | Decode %XX sequences |
| **HTML_ENTITY_DECODE** | Decode HTML entities |
| **COMPRESS_WHITE_SPACE** | Collapse whitespace |

