## 11. SSL / ACM Certificates

When adding a new domain to an ALB with WAF, the ALB HTTPS listener needs a certificate covering that domain.

| Scenario | What to do |
|----------|-----------|
| Wildcard cert exists (e.g. `*.example.com`) | Nothing — wildcard already covers `app.example.com` |
| No matching cert | Request one in ACM (same region as ALB). Validate via DNS or email. Attach to ALB HTTPS:443 listener. |
| Multiple domains on same ALB | ALB supports **SNI** — add multiple certs to the same HTTPS listener. ALB picks the right cert based on the Host header. |

**ACM request (CLI):**

```bash
aws acm request-certificate \
  --domain-name app.example.com \
  --validation-method DNS \
  --region ap-south-1
```

Then add the CNAME validation record to Route 53 (ACM shows you what to add).

