## 13. AWS CLI Commands

All commands assume `--scope REGIONAL` (for ALB/API Gateway). Use `--scope CLOUDFRONT` for CloudFront distributions.

### List Web ACLs

```bash
aws wafv2 list-web-acls --scope REGIONAL --region ap-south-1 --output table
```

### Get Web ACL (see all rules)

```bash
aws wafv2 get-web-acl \
  --scope REGIONAL \
  --id <WEB_ACL_ID> \
  --name <WEB_ACL_NAME> \
  --region ap-south-1
```

### List IP Sets

```bash
aws wafv2 list-ip-sets --scope REGIONAL --region ap-south-1 --output table
```

### Get IP Set (see all IPs/CIDRs)

```bash
aws wafv2 get-ip-set \
  --scope REGIONAL \
  --id <IP_SET_ID> \
  --name <IP_SET_NAME> \
  --region ap-south-1
```

### Create IP Set

```bash
aws wafv2 create-ip-set \
  --name my-ip-set \
  --scope REGIONAL \
  --ip-address-version IPV4 \
  --addresses "10.0.0.0/8" "192.168.1.0/24" \
  --region ap-south-1
```

### Update IP Set

```bash
# Get lock token first
LOCK_TOKEN=$(aws wafv2 get-ip-set --scope REGIONAL --id <ID> --name <NAME> --region ap-south-1 --query 'LockToken' --output text)

# Update (replaces entire list — include ALL addresses)
aws wafv2 update-ip-set \
  --scope REGIONAL \
  --id <ID> \
  --name <NAME> \
  --lock-token "$LOCK_TOKEN" \
  --addresses "10.0.0.0/8" "192.168.1.0/24" "203.0.113.0/32" \
  --region ap-south-1
```

### Check which ALB a Web ACL is attached to

```bash
aws wafv2 list-resources-for-web-acl \
  --web-acl-arn "arn:aws:wafv2:REGION:ACCOUNT:regional/webacl/NAME/UUID" \
  --resource-type APPLICATION_LOAD_BALANCER \
  --region ap-south-1
```

