## Quick Reference Card

### WAF Concepts

| Term | What it is |
|------|-----------|
| Web ACL | Container for rules; attached to ALB/CloudFront/API GW |
| Rule | Condition (Statement) + Action (Allow/Block/Count) + Priority |
| Statement | Condition: IP match, string match, geo, regex, rate, etc. |
| IP Set | Reusable list of IPs/CIDRs |
| Priority | Lower number = evaluated first; first match wins |
| Default Action | What happens when no rule matches (usually Allow) |

### Ports and Protocols

| Protocol | What WAF sees |
|----------|--------------|
| HTTP (80) | Full request: headers, URI, body, query, method |
| HTTPS (443) | Same (TLS terminates at ALB; WAF sees decrypted request) |

### Common Actions

| Action | Effect |
|--------|--------|
| **Allow** | Request passes to app |
| **Block** | 403 returned to client |
| **Count** | Request passes, but logged (for testing rules before enforcing) |

### End-to-End Flow

```
1. User types app.example.com
2. DNS (Route 53) → resolves to ALB
3. Browser → HTTPS → ALB (TLS terminates here)
4. ALB → Web ACL evaluates rules by priority
5. Rule matches? → Block (403) or Allow (forward to app)
6. No rule matches? → Default Action (Allow)
7. App returns response → ALB → User
```

